'''馬克西姆下水道'''（{{lang-it|Cloaca Maxima}}）是[[古羅馬|古羅馬]]時期羅馬的下水道系統。羅馬本來就位於濕地地帶，馬克西姆下水道將羅馬的污水排放至台伯河<ref>Aldrete, Gregory S. (2004). ''Daily life in the Roman city: Rome, Pompeii and Ostia''. Greenwood Publishing Group. ISBN 9780313331749, pp.34-35.</ref>。馬克西姆下水道修建於西元前600年時期<ref name="iath.virginia.edu">{{Cite web |url=http://www3.iath.virginia.edu/waters/Journal4Hopkins.pdf |title=Waters of Rome Journal - 4 - Hopkins.indd |access-date=2015-09-22 |archive-date=2021-05-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210504115037/http://www3.iath.virginia.edu/waters/Journal4Hopkins.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。馬克西姆下水道的建設僱用了伊特魯里亞人技術者，並半強制羅馬的貧民階級才得以實現。羅馬帝國各地的下水道均效仿了馬克西姆下水道<ref>Darvill, Timothy, Stamper, Paul and Timby, Jane (2002). ''England: an Oxford archaeological guide to sites from earliest times to AD 1600''. Oxford University Press. ISBN 9780192841018, pp. 162-163.</ref>。
